  <div class="hd">
    <h2>
      读书笔记&nbsp;&nbsp;· · · · · ·&nbsp;
          <span class="pl">(<a href="https://book.douban.com/subject/1382607/annotation">共<span property="v:count">44</span>篇</a>)</span>

    </h2>

      <a class="redbutt rr j a_show_login" href="https://www.douban.com/register?reason=annotate" rel="nofollow"><span>我来写笔记</span></a>
  </div>
  

    <div class="bd">
      <ul class="inline-tabs">
        <li class="on"><a href="#rank" id="by_rank" >按有用程度</a></li>
        <li><a href="#page" id="by_page" >按页码先后</a></li>
        <li><a href="#time" id="by_time" >最新笔记</a></li>
      </ul>
      
  <ul class="comments by_rank" >
      
      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="11575407">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/silenceapostle/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u42865180-151.jpg" alt="向沉默下拜" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11575407/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11575407/" class="">第50页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/silenceapostle/" class=" " title="向沉默下拜">向沉默下拜</a>
                (habitually contradictory)
              
                <span class="allstar50" title="力荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="11575407">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">为什么社会史这么快就失势呢？社会史的立论就是，社会结构是先于思想和行动存在的，而各种硬数据（hard data）则有通往这些解构的优先权。问题来了。

...the documents containing so-called &quot;hard data&quot; were themselves cultural products that required interpretation and critique.

John Scott在Gender and Politics of History里，将数据调查作成了极好的政治和文化解读，这样就把数据当成一种discourse而不...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2011-02-27 02:23</span>
                  
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="">1人喜欢</span>
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                为什么社会史这么快就失势呢？社会史的立论就是，社会结构是先于思想和行动存在的，而各种硬数据（hard data）则有通往这些解构的优先权。问题来了。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>...the documents containing so-called &quot;hard data&quot; were themselves cultural products that required interpretation and critique.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>John Scott在Gender and Politics of History里，将数据调查作成了极好的政治和文化解读，这样就把数据当成一种discourse而不是客观反映社会生活的数字。她还批判实证主义，说那些寻求无可厚非的数据的历史学家，不经阐述和质疑就使用文件记录了。她不是说数据没用，而只是要批驳那些简单引用数据将reality概念化的做法。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>但还有一个问题，一旦调查的种类接受批判和重新解读：（抱歉我真的不大明白只好照录了）<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>could the data it(指调查种类) reports be used in a statistically critical fashion - perhaps revealing patterns that are present in the data but obscured by the inquiry's procedures of classification and interpretation?</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>如果社会史是要将可量化的数据优先看做是客观体的话，文化史就在否定在文本中呈现的离散结构之外寻求reality的可能性。

                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







<div class="rec-sec">

    <span class="rec">

<a href="https://www.douban.com/accounts/register?reason=collect" class="j a_show_login lnk-sharing lnk-douban-sharing">推荐</a>
</span>
</div>

                  </div>
                <div class="pl col-time">
                  <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11575407/#comments">回应</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
                  2011-02-27 02:23
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>
      
      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="11547666">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/silenceapostle/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u42865180-151.jpg" alt="向沉默下拜" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11547666/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11547666/" class="">第40页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/silenceapostle/" class=" " title="向沉默下拜">向沉默下拜</a>
                (habitually contradictory)
              
                <span class="allstar50" title="力荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="11547666">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">1971年，Sewell完成博士论文，这时开始有感于实证主义的量化历史之局限性，和working model's内在的唯物决定论。他感觉量化法并不能解决人们何以理解结构带来的限制的问题，不能解决人们怎么创造历史的问题。Sewell现在回想：

I see my switch from social to cultural history as a belated working out of the anti-Fordist dimension of my 1960s radicalism...My own path out of the new social history's abstracted empi...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2011-02-25 15:34</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                1971年，Sewell完成博士论文，这时开始有感于实证主义的量化历史之局限性，和working model's内在的唯物决定论。他感觉量化法并不能解决人们何以理解结构带来的限制的问题，不能解决人们怎么创造历史的问题。Sewell现在回想：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>I see my switch from social to cultural history as a belated working out of the anti-Fordist dimension of my 1960s radicalism...My own path out of the new social history's abstracted empiricism...was inspired by cultural anthropology. What anthropology offered was a way of getting at meaningful human action.</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>文化人类学将这种意义历史扩大到思想家之外，这正是Sewell认为文化人类学的奇妙地方。说到底，之所以要这样做就是要解决文化问题。但这偏偏就和新社会史的实证主义认识论和客观本体论相悖。新社会史认为结构先于行动，而人类学则恰恰相反。所以Sewell一开始面临这种结合觉得很难适应。而且并不是所有社会学家都从文化人类学来完成文化转向。
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







<div class="rec-sec">

